column5: Tuesday I back out for steelies on the fly. I was out for a couple of hours and started fishing with a green/brown gold bead head wolley bugger  and hooked up with a big male
and the second was a sweet female that inhaled a gold bead head hares ear. While fliping over rocks I came across this nymph (stonefly) that was worth a picture
Very nice. I need to get back into fly fishing. I used to do it all the time.
Cool!  I have never busted out the fly rod for steelhead but I do want to.
that water looks awsome! nice fish too hen doesnt look spent yet.
Nice!  I'm looking forward to moving to the area soon and chasing steel on the fly...
pretty sly for a flyguy....nice shootin...
Stream Stripper where are you from?
